# Start
  `visited_start ?= false`
  `map_known ?= false`
  `lantern_lit ?= false`
  `coin ?= 0`
  > Rain taps against the shutters of the Hollow Bell inn.
  > `!visited_start` A sealed letter waits on your table. Its wax bears the mark of a crescent moon.
  + Open the letter *-> [.Letter]
  + Step into the village -> [Village]

## Letter
  `visited_start := true`
  `map_known := true`
  w-> [Inventory]("/widgets/inventory.saga")
  > The letter is brief: "Find the bell beneath the old watchtower before moonrise. Trust the woman with the blue scarf."
  > A charcoal map is sketched beneath the warning.
  -> [Village]

# Village
  `village_visits++`
  > The village of Brindlewick curls around a muddy square. Lanterns glow like fireflies in the rain.
  > `map_known` The charcoal map from the letter is already soft at the creases.
  + Visit the market square -> [Square]("/market.saga")
  + Walk to the old watchtower road -> `map_known` [Road]
  + `!map_known` Ask around for directions -> [.Directions]
  + `coin >= 2` Buy a dry cloak before leaving -> `coin >= 2` [Square.CloakSeller]("/market.saga")
  + Speak with the gate watch -> [.GateWatch]

## Directions
  `map_known := true`
  > A fishmonger points with his pipe. "Old road is north. Mind the stones. They listen."
  -> [Village]

## GateWatch
  > The watchman leans on his spear beneath the village arch.
  > `old_key` His eyes flick to the blackened key in your hand, then quickly away.
  + Ask about the watchtower -> [.WatchtowerRumor]
  + Return to the square -> [Village]

### WatchtowerRumor
  `heard_bell_rumor := true`
  > "No bell there now," he says. "Not above ground, anyway."
  + Press him for more *-> [..OldKey]
  + Thank him and leave -> [..]

### OldKey
  `old_key := true`
  > He slips a blackened key into your palm. "If the lower door still stands, this might remember it."
  -> [..]

# Road
  `road_steps++`
  > The northern road narrows between leaning birches. Somewhere ahead, stone shifts against stone.
  > `has_cloak` Rain beads on your borrowed cloak and rolls away instead of finding your collar.
  *-> `road_steps == 1` [.FirstSign]
  -> `lantern_lit` [Gate]("/ruins.saga")
  -> [.DarkRoad]

## FirstSign
  > A milestone turns as you pass it, revealing an arrow carved into its back.
  -> [Road]

## DarkRoad
  > Without a lit lantern, the trees knit themselves into a wall of black needles.
  + Return to Brindlewick -> [Village]
  + Try the road anyway -> `heard_bell_rumor` [Gate]("/ruins.saga")
